 <p><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" background="http://www.sebminas.com/eq/sig.jpg" width="490"><tr><td style=filter:glow(color="0080FF") valign="top"  height="10"><font size="3"><br><br>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<a style="font-weight:bold ;color:FFE8E8; text-decoration: none" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330">Noonie Violetskies</a></font></td></tr><tr><td height="116" valign="top"><font size="4" color="white"> <b>&nbspArch Mage of Thunderwalkers</b></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=baervon>Baervon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(10/8/02 4:47:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=376.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re:</span><hr size=1> Well, I've been playing my mage since Nov of 99. That makes me a pre-Kunark mage as far as I can remember. I remember tons of problems the mage class has come through and I really believe we have evolved into a completely new creature. To quote a commercial &quot;This is NOT your father's mage&quot;. Our focus seems to me to have switched away from damage as nukers to pet damage. Wether or not that is good depends on your play style I think. But I wanted to look at a few points here.<br>
<br>
Our damage is about 70/30 pet/nuke. At least epic is, I would say pre-epic it drops to 60/40. I just got my epic like last week so I still have the idea of what I was pre-epic FRESH in my mind. I just wanna interrupt this thought quickly and say HOLY HELL. I thought I was fully prepared as to the power of the epic but unless you control it and XP with it you have no idea of how NASTY it is. It soloed 3 dark blue mobs in Chardok. I just stood there, mouth agape. Epic is truly a whole new plateu of power for a mage and my god people, break your butts trying to get it. <br>
<br>
Ok back on topic.<br>
<br>
Let's take the average and say our ratio in a normal XP grind is 65/35 pet/nuke. (I'll be totally honest and say when I XP with my epic it's more like 80/20 but I digress) Our nukes seem to be set up with that sort of ratio in mind. What I mean is, for them to flip the power balance to 65/35 NUKE/pet, wouldn't they have to WEAKEN our pets?? See my point? If they boost our nukes and leave pets the same, it'll be more like 65/55 pet/nuke. Boosting our nukes significantly would have the effect of super-powering us if the pets were left the same. I really don't think we want our pets downgraded, especially since Verant just went to all the problem of souping up the pets. I don't think Verant wants that either. This leads us to 2 options, at least as far as I can see:<br>
<br>
1) Verant is gonna totally screw us by giving us new, weak pets and bad nukes combined. We all quit in disgust.<br>
<br>
Or the slightly more realistic (I hope) option 2<br>
<br>
2) Our new pets are stronger than epic (which I truly believe they will be) and make up the difference of our less powerfull nukes. <br>
<br>
I have personally experienced every curve ball they have thrown mages (except the rain nerf, I did not actually SEE the rains hit as many mobs as they wanted in 3 waves heh). I remember when pets had no procs. I remember when we did not dual wield unless you gave them weapons. I remember the swords of runes proccing on EVERYTHING (damn that was nice). I have also lived through every expansion. I honestly and truly think that each expansion has been better than the last, and fewer mistakes from a balance perspective have been made. I have high hopes for this new expansion, and for one, will enjoy the challenge of fitting my mage into the new game that evolves. I think some posters have forgotten that part of the fun of EQ. C'est la vie.<br>
<br>
Baervon<br>
Proud lvl 60 epicced mage of Quellious<br>
